00:17:24,220 --> 00:17:25,820
and playing football, listen,

292
00:17:25,820 --> 00:17:27,740
they never let any of us go out there

293
00:17:27,740 --> 00:17:29,240
without a helmet on and play.

294
00:17:30,380 --> 00:17:31,680
They just didn't do it.

295
00:17:31,680 --> 00:17:33,600
In fact, when I played high school football,

296
00:17:33,600 --> 00:17:35,780
if someone's helmet came off during the play,

297
00:17:35,780 --> 00:17:37,180
they had to sit out of play

298
00:17:37,180 --> 00:17:38,860
and get some kind of equipment manager

299
00:17:38,860 --> 00:17:41,540
to check that thing out to make sure that it was secure,

300
00:17:41,540 --> 00:17:43,140
that they'd be able to play again.

301
00:17:43,860 --> 00:17:45,900
And we find that, listen, as the people of God,

302
00:17:45,900 --> 00:17:49,260
why is it that we would bypass the armor of God

303
00:17:49,260 --> 00:17:53,060
and not understand the importance of what God has given us

304
00:17:53,060 --> 00:17:55,660
that if we're going to stand,

305
00:17:55,660 --> 00:17:57,740
we must put on the whole armor of God?

306
00:17:58,740 --> 00:17:59,860
To stand in the gap,

307
00:17:59,860 --> 00:18:03,220
we must first stand for truth and for right.

308
00:18:03,220 --> 00:18:05,760
And in order to stand for truth and right,

309
00:18:05,760 --> 00:18:07,980
we must have the whole armor of God.

310
00:18:09,300 --> 00:18:11,700
There's a battle that is raging.

311
00:18:13,460 --> 00:18:16,460
God's looking for some people that would stand in the gap,

312
00:18:17,340 --> 00:18:21,060
that would stand for truth and for right.

313
00:18:21,060 --> 00:18:24,060
We find that not only would a man

